On my trip to Nashville I popped into the @thenashvillefoodproject where they were working hard to get meals ready for the afternoon food delivery! And as you can see, I was on crouton duty. 

In 2022, Nashville Food Project cooked an average of 5,582 meals a week!! They provide healthy, made from scratch meals for their community. While also minimizing food waste! 

@thenashvillefoodproject knows that by providing meals to those who don’t know where their next meal will come from, they are cultivating a thriving community. One that disrupts cycles of poverty and food scarcity. Food, and healthy food especially, is crucial for our development. 

 Thank you so much @thenashvillefoodproject for all the hard work and innovative thinking. Your love and action in your community has inspired me and I look forward to coming back.

Life has been moving at full speed these days and I hate to admit it, but my joints are starting to ache! 

Often in times of stress and business my autoimmune disorder, psoriasis, likes to show up. I’ve spent a little shy of 10 years learning how to mitigate stress and immune system. But sometimes life is just that: stressful and fast! And that’s okay. 

Here are my best tips to manage an autoimmune disorder: 

1. Gluten might be the biggest problem. When I cut it out of my diet most of my symptoms seemingly vanished. And of course, from time to time I eat a little gluten. I mean, you all just watch me make homemade pasta! 
It’s when im eating excessive gluten that the problem is out of control. 

2. Anti-inflammatory foods are a gift from the universe that you should take full advantage of. We’re talking salmon, celery, ginger, pineapple, and many many more! 

3. Keep track of when you’re sick/having symptoms. This will tell you if it’s the food that’s upsetting you or maybe an environment or person you frequent. Track the pattern and adjust your routine to see if it helps! 

#healingfoods #autoimune #stressmanagement #stressrelief #psoriasis #juice #celeryjuice #celeryjuicebenefits

Fall is here and so are stuffy noses! This morning I whipped up the perfect fall remedy. I used whatever was in her fridge. 

This is one of those “no recipe” recipes. So just follow your gut and whatever veggies you have! *adding chicken would increase the protein (but we are vegetarian in this house)* 

-onion
-garlic
(Simmer until fragrant) 
(Next add whatever veggies will take the longest to cook and let them each simmer for a couple min before adding more) 

-celery
-carrots 
-bell peppers 
-butternut squash 
-tomatoes
-cabbage 

-lemon juice 
-Italian herbs 
-dash of cayenne 
-salt and pepper 

Save this for the next time you are feeling under the weather! 

#naturalremedy #souprecipe #comfortfood #healingfoods #wellness #naturalmedicine

Spent the week creating art 💝

This past year (exactly one year last week) I sat on my best friends bed and wrote the book Strong Girls, start to finish. 
After teaching at my siblings high school I was left wanting to help more. Wanting to encourage young girls who were once just like me. Wanting to make them believe in themselves the way I believe in them. 
Over the next  year I poured every last little thing, thought, topic I knew about being a Strong Girl onto a page. Creating my first book, Strong Girls. 
A book written for every little girl of every size, color, and place. A book she can read that fills her with self confidence and peace as life ebbs and flows. 
This book is for the younger version of you and every girl that comes next. ❤️💛💚💙💜
Available on Amazon this Sunday, 11/26/23.

MONTH 9 OF MY FASHION DETOX 

9 long months of not buying any fast fashion…. Just kidding! 

Giving up fast fashion has been way easier than giving up gluten. 😂 right now I only buy from second hand platforms and sustainable companies. 

Winter is officially here. Leading me to have to find eco friendly winter wear. Look no further, I have found the perfect jacket! 

@therecycledplanet is a great new sustainable company and I could not be more happy with this jacket! It keeps me warm, is easy to clean, and fits over all my layers. 

This is a size small (I’m 5’3, usually wear a US 2-4). I would get a smaller size if I wasn’t planning on wearing it over all my sweaters!

Rainy day story time 🏡

Food shopping: small town edition. 
The nearest grocery store is about 10 miles away- which is a 20 minute drive through a mountain, along a creek. 

So with 5 acres and 6 green thumbs my family has been gardening for a very long time. Generations! A lot of our recipes have been handed down from the women who came before us. 

Eating from the garden every day is a sustainable alternative to traditional shopping. Not to mention, there’s nothing more exciting than watching the plants you grow. 

Here in Vermont we eat seed to plate!

A few weeks late but better late than never! 

Late last year I competed at Miss Earth USA representing my home state- Vermont. 

You see, Vermont is not known for pageantry. We may hold the most miss congenitality titles (5), but we’ve only ever won one national title, in 1955. In fact Vermont Earth doesn’t even have a state director! 

So entering this national stage I knew what the odds were. I took every little bit of Vermont I could, and showed our country just what we believe in. 

⛰️We believe in protecting our planet. 

🏔️We believe in staying authentic to ourselves. 

🏔️We believe in educating our children. 

And with these beliefs, and my community, and most importantly my family, I had a national platform to highlight these concepts before our peers. Showing them there is hope for a greener tomorrow. There is hope to be your real self. There is hope that education will stop coming with such a high price. 

So I just want to say thank you, to all of you who made me who I am. Who taught me along the way and cheered from the sidelines. It’s this support and my experience as a Vermonter that equipped me with the skills to advocate for what we believe in. 

It’s the greatest honor to receive awards for interview and leadership @missearthusa 
 
These awards validated that Vermont has a voice and a unique perspective that can transform our country. 

And guess what? Strong Girls, THEY’RE GOING TO CHANGE THE WORLD! 

Thank you all!! 🧡💙💛💚
